.SH NAME
.PP
\f[B]tpm2_stirrandom\f[R](1) \- Add \[lq]additional information\[rq]
into TPM RNG state.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]tpm2_stirrandom\f[R] [\f[I]OPTIONS\f[R]] [\f[I]ARGUMENT\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]tpm2_stirrandom\f[R](1) \- Inject \[lq]additional information\[rq]
as bytes into TPM entropy Protected Capability pool.
.PP
\[lq]Additional information\[rq] can be extracted from file specified as
argument or being read from \f[I]STDIN\f[R] if argument is not
specified.
.PP
Up to 128 bytes can be injected at once through standard input to
\f[B]tpm2_stirrandom\f[R](1).
.PP
If input file is larger than 128 bytes, \f[B]tpm2_stirrandom\f[R](1)
will fail.
.PP
Adding data through \f[B]tpm2_stirrandom\f[R](1) will trigger a
reseeding of TPM DRBG Protected Capability.
It is used when performing any sensitive action on a shielded location
such as loading a persistent key or acting on a Protected Capability
like updating TPM firmware.
